    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they both have \"principles\" but in a real debate judge isn't just gonna let us say \"it depends.\" i need to know which one is actually more logically sound. like, if you look at it from a purely ethical standpoint, isn't it harder to justify a border that keeps people in danger than it is to justify a law that is just about administrative consistency? isn't the humanitarian side basically the \"correct\" moral answer here?",
